{"id_": "3313e93c-9904-4925-ad48-3ab6b2e58fa6", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"header_path": "/"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "e68b06b4-2dce-458d-a3c7-c6568f54ac82", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {}, "hash": "0f35435b93d0489c7e50589caaedf4396a0be373980e517e7769b52e3594d3b0", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "2d5f79a5-a250-48e9-acc6-33882e71afb6", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"header_path": "/ANNEX F-1: STRENGTHENING AND RATIONALISING OUR RETIREMENT SYSTEM/"}, "hash": "0e5739d4b23c05e9054a81945d785f3e9b41b6ae7d9babf83e8baf0f34e81ac1", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "text": "# ANNEX F-1: STRENGTHENING AND RATIONALISING OUR RETIREMENT SYSTEM

The Government will make adjustments to the CPF system to strengthen assurance for retirement:

- **(A)** Increase in senior workers’ CPF contribution rates;
- **(B)** Increase in the Enhanced Retirement Sum; and
- **(C)** Closure of the CPF Special Account for members aged 55 and above.

The following Budget 2024 initiatives will also strengthen retirement support for seniors who need more help:

- **(D)** Enhancements to the Silver Support Scheme; and
- **(E)** Enhancements to the Matched Retirement Savings Scheme.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 3, "end_char_idx": 593, "text_template": "{metadata_str}

{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "
", "class_name": "TextNode"}

{"id_": "2d5f79a5-a250-48e9-acc6-33882e71afb6", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"header_path": "/ANNEX F-1: STRENGTHENING AND RATIONALISING OUR RETIREMENT SYSTEM/"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "e68b06b4-2dce-458d-a3c7-c6568f54ac82", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {}, "hash": "0f35435b93d0489c7e50589caaedf4396a0be373980e517e7769b52e3594d3b0", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "3313e93c-9904-4925-ad48-3ab6b2e58fa6", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"header_path": "/"}, "hash": "a080d1260c9fc218a27264813429fd4bf374a78e693ac39bb7e6178e73dbc026", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "d3883ad1-8578-47e9-9ba6-dfe7943d2f83", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"header_path": "/ANNEX F-1: STRENGTHENING AND RATIONALISING OUR RETIREMENT SYSTEM/(A) Increase in Senior Workers’ CPF Contribution Rates/"}, "hash": "2953f7a3e62fb16a809d6eebe33cc48be67c7ab2468d4ada02ab1ab12ae10fc8", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "text": "## (A) Increase in Senior Workers’ CPF Contribution Rates

In line with the recommendation from the Tripartite Workgroup on Older Workers in 2019, the Government announced that CPF contribution rates will be raised gradually over the next decade or so for Singaporean and Permanent Resident workers aged above 55 to 70 (see Table 1). When the increases have been fully implemented, those aged above 55 to 60 will have the same CPF contribution rates as younger workers.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 595, "end_char_idx": 1064, "text_template": "{metadata_str}

