{"id_": "e9526913-ce12-4680-8d31-736c28cde176", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"header_path": "/ANNEX F-1: STRENGTHENING AND RATIONALISING OUR RETIREMENT SYSTEM/"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "e68b06b4-2dce-458d-a3c7-c6568f54ac82", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {}, "hash": "0f35435b93d0489c7e50589caaedf4396a0be373980e517e7769b52e3594d3b0", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "5646a38a-e9df-4ff9-8cc5-7c3f823301a0", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"header_path": "/ANNEX F-1: STRENGTHENING AND RATIONALISING OUR RETIREMENT SYSTEM/"}, "hash": "bd4c10226aa49cdbc2cb8cff46f88ff7eab517d5bba421d9c8b42746e4574142", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "23de515a-c6dd-42d3-97b3-9f55ae0dafdd", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"header_path": "/ANNEX F-1: STRENGTHENING AND RATIONALISING OUR RETIREMENT SYSTEM/"}, "hash": "fd41d96d4594db6ddee35508aa4d10d224c8f4bf174675d4534a67a88d3fc67f", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "text": "## (B) Increase in Enhanced Retirement Sum (“ERS”)

The ERS is the maximum amount of savings that members aged 55 and above can place in their CPF Retirement Account (“RA”) to earn RA interest rates and receive CPF monthly payouts. Today, the ERS is set at three times the Basic Retirement Sum (“BRS”).

The Government will raise the ERS from three times the BRS to four times, from 1 January 2025 (see Table 3). This will allow CPF members to voluntarily top up more to their RA, by transferring their Ordinary Account (“OA”) savings or by making cash top-ups, in order to receive higher CPF monthly payouts in their retirement.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 4714, "end_char_idx": 5343, "text_template": "{metadata_str}

{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "
", "class_name": "TextNode"}

