{"id_": "734eaa19-3849-4c8b-bf8c-e849a188de9c", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"header_path": "/ANNEX B-2: ENTERPRISE SUPPORT PACKAGE/"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "3a0e3eb9-680e-41f6-9620-991849cfed92", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {}, "hash": "d787fcbb48f92cc638d2b8925eba4394a6ad0930b4a5fe147d1956ece90999be", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "6993717e-87ca-4383-bf20-c7323b6389f2", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"header_path": "/"}, "hash": "4e97ce1c957e5b7bdc806158b8ebc6e571d244546cc0997a9665d3a6da9d1084", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "08524078-2d10-4354-a0e6-53f69df5faf9", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"header_path": "/ANNEX B-2: ENTERPRISE SUPPORT PACKAGE/(A) Corporate Income Tax (“CIT”) Rebate/"}, "hash": "12ae16b2a02b86de9a9a3edd5bcd0522cc7ffc2ed27e93b73088a3a45a71002f", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "text": "## (A) Corporate Income Tax (“CIT”) Rebate

To help businesses manage rising costs, a CIT Rebate of 50% tax payable will be granted for the Year of Assessment (“YA”) 2024.

Companies that have employed at least one local employee in 2023 (referred to as “local employee condition”) will receive a minimum benefit of $2,000 in the form of a cash payout (referred to as “CIT Rebate Cash Grant”).

Companies that have met the local employee condition will automatically receive the CIT Rebate Cash Grant by 3Q 2024. The CIT Rebate, less any CIT Rebate Cash Grant received, will be automatically incorporated in the companies’ tax assessments raised after they file their CIT returns for YA 2024.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 329, "end_char_idx": 1021, "text_template": "{metadata_str}

{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "
", "class_name": "TextNode"}

{"id_": "43a0af1b-2783-4b5a-bdea-8d55d2dea778", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"header_path": "/ANNEX B-2: ENTERPRISE SUPPORT PACKAGE/"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "3a0e3eb9-680e-41f6-9620-991849cfed92", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {}, "hash": "d787fcbb48f92cc638d2b8925eba4394a6ad0930b4a5fe147d1956ece90999be", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "08524078-2d10-4354-a0e6-53f69df5faf9", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"header_path": "/ANNEX B-2: ENTERPRISE SUPPORT PACKAGE/(A) Corporate Income Tax (“CIT”) Rebate/"}, "hash": "12ae16b2a02b86de9a9a3edd5bcd0522cc7ffc2ed27e93b73088a3a45a71002f", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "e4ec4d67-ec5f-4bef-9465-ac6dff9a84bb", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"header_path": "/ANNEX B-2: ENTERPRISE SUPPORT PACKAGE/"}, "hash": "338d8a730882063e58824e48e1b2b247d7b98d019c2e99390c429a2939081d3a", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "text": "## (B) Enhancements to the Enterprise Financing Scheme (“EFS”)

The EFS enables Singapore enterprises to access financing more readily across all stages of growth. There will be three enhancements to the EFS under the Enterprise Support Package.

1. The maximum loan quantum under the EFS – SME Working Capital Loan will be permanently enhanced from **$300,000** to **$500,000**. This will help SMEs to meet their increased working capital and operational cashflow needs, especially amid elevated costs.

2. The enhanced maximum loan quantum under the EFS – Trade Loan of **$10 million** will be extended till **31 March 2025**. This will support businesses’ internationalisation efforts amid global supply chain disruptions.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 1742, "end_char_idx": 2467, "text_template": "{metadata_str}

{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "
", "class_name": "TextNode"}

