{"id_": "c7e8a5f1-57bb-4896-ace9-5e95cb65ce32", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"header_path": "/ANNEX D-1: SKILLSFUTURE LEVEL-UP PROGRAMME/"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "13960a20-0fad-477c-8631-b5a81e3f3119", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {}, "hash": "9d07034250383ca32c8ae0a406cf5057649afad72b6d7f6e10d59a08a8560acb", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "587caa04-dc29-489d-8e77-d8449150bf18", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"header_path": "/"}, "hash": "0df0a07f2799031e7890636066cd781b8f03b5bbcfa62a18ff0516fedd4161a4", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "f9f3558b-5a30-457d-8d14-fc3db3316160", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"header_path": "/ANNEX D-1: SKILLSFUTURE LEVEL-UP PROGRAMME/"}, "hash": "114002584c85cddfc7284c8ce2dda461ee328c2a6d16ece73fa228b15a755bc7", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "text": "## (A) $4,000 SkillsFuture Credit (“SFC”) (Mid-Career) Top-Up

The SFC was introduced at Budget 2015 to encourage Singaporeans to take ownership of their skills development. To provide more support for mid-career Singaporeans, we will provide a $4,000 SFC (Mid-Career) top-up to every Singaporean in the year they turn 40 years old. Singaporeans currently aged 40 and above will receive the top-up in May 2024. The credit will have no expiry date.

Eligible individuals can use the SFC top-up for selected courses that are industry-oriented and have better employability outcomes. More details on eligible courses will be announced at the MOE Committee of Supply.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 568, "end_char_idx": 1231, "text_template": "{metadata_str}

{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "
", "class_name": "TextNode"}

{"id_": "f9f3558b-5a30-457d-8d14-fc3db3316160", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"header_path": "/ANNEX D-1: SKILLSFUTURE LEVEL-UP PROGRAMME/"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "13960a20-0fad-477c-8631-b5a81e3f3119", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {}, "hash": "9d07034250383ca32c8ae0a406cf5057649afad72b6d7f6e10d59a08a8560acb", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "c7e8a5f1-57bb-4896-ace9-5e95cb65ce32", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"header_path": "/ANNEX D-1: SKILLSFUTURE LEVEL-UP PROGRAMME/"}, "hash": "4858876843c8fae772f77184152117a443cff0415a4c71a183318b3a3051e0e3", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "df720d34-e9d4-4324-8d40-fd324b63c49f", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"header_path": "/ANNEX D-1: SKILLSFUTURE LEVEL-UP PROGRAMME/"}, "hash": "d44221ceaf6f45f50a1574dd1b7f7ea53760178c7f3c69e77b24e021622db751", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "text": "## (B) Support for Singaporeans to pursue another subsidised Full-Time Diploma

Currently, individuals who have previously received MOE subsidies or Government sponsorship for a diploma or higher qualification (e.g., degree) are not eligible for another subsidised full-time diploma qualification at our institutions.

From Academic Year 2025, Singaporeans aged 40 and above will qualify for the Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy for another subsidised full-time diploma at our Polytechnics, ITE, and Arts Institutions (i.e., Nanyang Academy of Fine Arts and LASALLE College of the Arts). This will expand the opportunities available for mid-career Singaporeans to take subsidised courses.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 1233, "end_char_idx": 1916, "text_template": "{metadata_str}

{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "
", "class_name": "TextNode"}

{"id_": "39e88bd8-6b5e-4766-95bf-da79e025e237", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"header_path": "/ANNEX D-1: SKILLSFUTURE LEVEL-UP PROGRAMME/"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "13960a20-0fad-477c-8631-b5a81e3f3119", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {}, "hash": "9d07034250383ca32c8ae0a406cf5057649afad72b6d7f6e10d59a08a8560acb", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "df720d34-e9d4-4324-8d40-fd324b63c49f", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"header_path": "/ANNEX D-1: SKILLSFUTURE LEVEL-UP PROGRAMME/"}, "hash": "d44221ceaf6f45f50a1574dd1b7f7ea53760178c7f3c69e77b24e021622db751", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "891fa4d0-1636-45b1-9e50-1ed696ba0140", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"header_path": "/ANNEX D-1: SKILLSFUTURE LEVEL-UP PROGRAMME/"}, "hash": "24b900e98f56e6ede519675a8b4aa5b01d804e08cec43be5455b51d7c34a70f9", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "text": "## Training Allowance Details

The training allowance will be equivalent to 50% of the individual’s average income over the latest available 12-month period, capped at $3,000 per month. Every individual can receive up to 24 months of training allowance throughout their lifetime.

More details will be provided at the MOE Committee of Supply.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 2849, "end_char_idx": 3191, "text_template": "{metadata_str}

{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "
", "class_name": "TextNode"}

